name: in-ver-flow
description: This is a digital art piece I created on 2nd August 2006 at 12:03pm using an old school program called Roxio Photosuite as part of my 'Flashcore x photography' collection. Something I made when I was 15 years old as an aspiring artist and photographer, but never published. I’m now 30 and am finally sharing this piece and many more I’ve found from my old CD and USB drives. This is a photo of some flowers in my Nan’s garden. I then edited it in Photosuite to create an inverted glitch piece, in pastel colours. I did a few in different colours and have minted a vivid purple vision on my main account objkt/96705.
